<Link id="l01197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1197"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Cache type for the splitBlock function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1198" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph/#afc87be5343187a4cef74ac1a22d4a2b2"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">using </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph/#afc87be5343187a4cef74ac1a22d4a2b2">SplitBlockCache</a> = std::optional&lt;SmallVector&lt;Symbol &#42;, 8&gt;&gt;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1199"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Splits block B into a sequence of smaller blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1201"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// SplitOffsets should be a sequence of ascending offsets in B. The starting</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// offset should be greater than zero, and the final offset less than</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1204"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// B.getSize() - 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1205"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1206"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The resulting seqeunce of blocks will start with the original block B</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1207"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// (truncated to end at the first split offset) followed by newly introduced</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1208"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// blocks starting at the subsequent split points.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1209"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1210"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The optional Cache parameter can be used to speed up repeated calls to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1211"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// splitBlock for blocks within a single Section. If the value is None then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1212"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the cache will be treated as uninitialized and splitBlock will populate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1213"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// it. Otherwise it is assumed to contain the list of Symbols pointing at B,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1214"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// sorted in descending order of offset.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1215"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1216"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1217"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Notes:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1218"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1219"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// 1 splitBlock must be used with care. Splitting a block may cause</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1220"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    incoming edges to become invalid if the edge target subexpression</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1221"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    points outside the bounds of the newly split target block (E.g. an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1222"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    edge &#39;S + 10 : Pointer64&#39; where S points to a newly split block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1223"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    whose size is less than 10). No attempt is made to detect invalidation</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1224"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    of incoming edges, as in general this requires context that the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1225"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    LinkGraph does not have. Clients are responsible for ensuring that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1226"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    splitBlock is not used in a way that invalidates edges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1227"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1228"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// 2 The newly introduced blocks will have new ordinals that will be higher</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1229"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    than any other ordinals in the section. Clients are responsible for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1230"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    re-assigning block ordinals to restore a compatible order if needed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1231"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1232"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// 3 The cache is not automatically updated if new symbols are introduced</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1233"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    between calls to splitBlock. Any newly introduced symbols may be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1234"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    added to the cache manually (descending offset order must be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1235"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///    preserved), or the cache can be set to None and rebuilt by</span></CodeLine>
